# Sports Arbitrage App - Environment Variables
# ============================================

# The Odds API Configuration (REQUIRED)
ODDS_API_KEY=your_odds_api_key_here

# Supabase Configuration (Optional - for user authentication)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url_here
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Frontend API Server URL (for production)
# For Netlify: https://your-site-name.netlify.app
# For Vercel: https://your-vercel-domain.vercel.app
VITE_PROXY_SERVER=https://your-site-name.netlify.app

# Instructions:
# ============

# FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Update the values with your actual credentials
# 3. Run: npm run dev

# FOR NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. Go to: https://app.netlify.com/
# 2. Navigate to: Site settings → Environment variables
# 3. Add all variables above (except VITE_PROXY_SERVER - this will be your Netlify URL)
# 4. Get your Odds API key from: https://the-odds-api.com/
# 5. Deploy using: ./deploy-to-netlify.sh

# FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT (Legacy):
# 1. Go to your Vercel dashboard: https://vercel.com/dashboard
# 2. Navigate to: Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add all variables above
# 4. Replace "your-vercel-domain" with your actual Vercel deployment URL

# PLATFORM COMPARISON:
# ===================
# ✅ Netlify (Recommended):
#    - Better function handling
#    - More generous free tier
#    - Better DX for static sites
#    - Enhanced security features
#
# ⚠️ Vercel (Legacy):
#    - Good for Next.js apps
#    - Limited function execution time
#    - More restrictive free tier 